telemessage

Class TeleMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • telemessage.TeleMessage

  • public class TeleMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents container for message to be send via TeleMessage. Class wraps message and converts it to chosen format, i.e. XML, JSON or URL Receiving message is possible only for XML and JSON
    Since:
    5/26/2014.

      • writeSend

        public Result writeSend(java.lang.String username,
               java.lang.String password,
               TeleMessage.Interface anInterface,
               java.io.OutputStream out)
                 throws java.io.IOException,
                        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Prepares message request to be sent. There are 3 options (indicated by anInterface TeleMessage.Interface parameter): 1. XML - writes xml into OutputStream out 2. JSON - writes json into 3. SEND_TO_URL - populate and return result with Map of parameters to be sent over URL. This options doesn't support multi recipients and files
        Parameters:
        username - TeleMessage username
        password - TeleMessage password
        anInterface - interface to prepare message for
        out - output stream to write into
        Returns:
        result
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if any IO exception thrown
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if message is absence some data

      • writeQueryStatus

        public Result writeQueryStatus(java.lang.String username,
                      java.lang.String password,
                      long messageID,
                      java.lang.String messageKey,
                      TeleMessage.Interface anInterface,
                      java.io.OutputStream out)
                        throws java.io.IOException,
                               java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Prepares status request to be sent. There are 2 options (indicated by anInterface TeleMessage.Interface parameter): 1. XML - writes xml into OutputStream out 2. JSON - writes json into
        Parameters:
        username - user's username to get status for
        password - user's password to get status for
        messageID - message id, received by sending message
        messageKey - message key, received by sending message
        anInterface - interface to use (REST or XML)
        out - output stream to write result in
        Returns:
        Result if TeleMessage server responded to request
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
